Program: Omnibus
Title: Yuko Tojo
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376m04
Last Broadcast Date: 15 October 1999
Yuko Tojo was the grandchild of Japanese wartime prime minister General Hideki Tōjō, who was hung for war crimes. As a child, she was told only that "he died for his country". She descibes the hatred towards her family from society.